Message.MsgText: DBLOCK_FAILED_SIMS1593=CWSIS1593I: The messaging engine, ME_UUID={0}, INC_UUID={1}, has failed to gain an initial lock on the data store.
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine, identified by the UUIDs in the message, has been unable to get an exclusive lock on the database tables that hold its data. This could be due to another instance of the messaging engine running against the same set of tables. It could also be the result of a lock from a previously running instance being held for longer than expected in the database. The messaging engine will retry for a period during startup to see if it is able to acquire the lock.
Message.UserResponse: If the messaging engine does not succeed in acquiring the lock during the startup retry period then check that no other instance of the messaging engine is running and that there are no outstanding locks on the tables for this messaging engine being held on your database server.

Message.MsgText: DATASOURCE_NOT_FOUND_EXCEPTION_SIMS1524=CWSIS1524E: Data source, {0}, not found.
Message.Explanation: The look up of the specified JNDI name has failed to locate the data source.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the JNDI name is valid and try again.

Message.MsgText: DYNAMIC_TABLE_CREATION_EXCEPTION_SIMS1523=CWSIS1523E: Dynamic allocation of database objects in DB2 for z/OS is not allowed.
Message.Explanation: Database tables required by the data store cannot be created dynamically.
Message.UserResponse: Use the sibDDLGenerator tool to generate the DDL statements for the data store tables.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_NUMBER_OF_TEMPORARY_TABLES_SIMS1511=CWSIS1511E: An incorrect number of temporary tables, {0}, were found.
Message.Explanation: There must be at least one temporary table.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the problem and try again.

Message.MsgText: MAX_NUMBER_OF_TABLES_EXCEEDED_SIMS1541=CWSIS1541E: The maximum number of SIBnnn tables that can be used by a messaging engine, {0}, has been exceeded.
Message.Explanation: The total number of stream (there is always one stream table), permanent and temporary tables should not exceed the maximum.
Message.UserResponse: Reduce the number of permanent or temporary tables specified, and restart the server.

Message.MsgText: DBLOCK_VERSION_DOESNT_MATCH_SIMS1536=CWSIS1536E: The messaging engine''s version does not match that found in the data store. VERSION={0}, VERSION(DB)={1}
Message.Explanation: The version of your messaging engine does not match that in the data store.
Message.UserResponse: You are trying to connect to an existing set of database tables that are owned by a different messaging engine. Either point your messaging engine's data source to a separate set of tables or remove the existing ones.

Message.MsgText: CACHE_LOADER_TERMINATED_SIMS2003=CWSIS2003E: The cache loader daemon ended abnormally due to an unexpected exception: {0}
Message.Explanation: The cache loader daemon thread was interrupted and has stopped.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: EXPECTED_COLUMN_NOT_FOUND_SIMS1529=CWSIS1529E: The column, {0}, was not found in the table, {1}, as expected.
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine expected to find the column in the relevant table.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the problem and try again.

Message.MsgText: FILE_STORE_LOCK_VERSION_DOESNT_MATCH_SIMS1562=CWSIS1562E: The messaging engine''s version does not match that found in the file store. VERSION={0}, VERSION(FS)={1}
Message.Explanation: The version of your messaging engine does not match that in the file store.
Message.UserResponse: You are trying to connect to an existing set of files that are owned by a different messaging engine. Either point your messaging engine's file store to a separate set of files or remove the existing ones.

Message.MsgText: FILE_STORE_PERMANENT_STORE_SIZE_CURRENT_INFO_SIMS1551=CWSIS1551I: The current minimum reserved size of the permanent store file is {0} bytes. The current maximum size is {1} bytes.
Message.Explanation: This is part of the configuration information of the file store.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: STREAM_NOT_EMPTY_SIMS0507=CWSIS0507E: It is not possible to delete a stream that is not empty. Items on stream={0}. Stream class={1}
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to delete a stream that was not empty. The number of items remaining on the stream and it's type are supplied in the message to help determine the reason this operation was attempted.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: STREAM_NOT_EMPTY_SIMS0501=CWSIS0501E: It is not possible to delete a stream that is not empty.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to delete a stream that was not empty.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: SCHEMA_NAME_UNDEFINED_SIMS1547=CWSIS1547E: Unable to determine the schema name for the messaging engine.
Message.Explanation: The schema name was not defined explicitly for the data store, and the database user id was not provided.
Message.UserResponse: Provide a schema name and try again.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAMETER_COMBINATION_SIMS1595=CWSIS1595E: An invalid combination of parameters has been specified, Database: {0}, version: {1}, platform: {2} . Refer to the documentation for the correct parameters for your database.
Message.Explanation: The combination of parameters used was unrecognized by the sibDDLGenerator.
Message.UserResponse: Refer to the documentation for a valid combination of parameters to use for your database. Rerun the command with a valid combination of parameters.

Message.MsgText: FILE_STORE_START_PERMANENT_TEMPORARY_STORES_SIMS1585=CWSIS1585I: The file store is attempting to start its permanent store ({0}) and temporary store ({1}).
Message.Explanation: The file store is going to attempt to open and read the contents of its store files. If this is the first time the messaging engine has been started the files will also be created.
Message.UserResponse: No action is required.

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_OBTAIN_FILE_STORE_LOCK_SIMS1567=CWSIS1567E: Messaging engine {0} cannot obtain the lock on its file store, which ensures it has exclusive access to the data.
Message.Explanation: The file store lock is already held, probably by another active or recently failed messaging engine.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: INVALID_MSGSTORE_STATE_SIMS0505=CWSIS0505E: The data store is in an incorrect state, {0}.
Message.Explanation: The data store is not in the correct state to perform the requested operation.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_ROLLBACK_COMPLETE_SIMS1005=CWSIS1005E: The transaction cannot be rolled back. The transaction is complete or completing.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to roll back a transaction that has already been completed or is in the process of completing.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: FILE_STORE_PERMANENT_STORE_FULL_SIMS1574E=CWSIS1574E: The file store's permanent store file is full.
Message.Explanation: The file store has no more space in the permanent store file to store messages. This could be due to an unexpected build up of messages or the file size being too small.
Message.UserResponse: Clean up any excess messages or if necessary increase the size of the permanent store file.

Message.MsgText: SPILL_DISPATCHER_IS_FULL_SIMS1576E=CWSIS1576E: The spill dispatcher is full.
Message.Explanation: The spill dispatcher is full and cannot accept any new messages until some space has been made available. Removal of existing messages will be allowed to help the dispatcher free up space.
Message.UserResponse: No action should be required to return the dispatcher to normal. However This may be a symptom of your temporary store file size being too small.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TABLE_TYPE_EXCEPTION_SIMS1525=CWSIS1525E: Incorrect item table type, {0}.
Message.Explanation: An item table type has not been recognized as valid.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the problem and try again.

Message.MsgText: STREAM_ADD_CONFLICT_SIMS0005=CWSIS0005E: It is not possible to add {0} to second stream {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to add an item to a stream when the item was already in another stream.

Message.MsgText: DATASTORE_LOCK_REENABLED_CWSIS1598=CWSIS1598I: The data store exclusive lock has been automatically re-enabled.

Message.MsgText: DUPLICATE_EXPIRABLE_SIMS2000=CWSIS2000E: The item does not have a unique key: {0}

Message.MsgText: DATASOURCE_EXCEPTION_SIMS1501=CWSIS1501E: The data source has produced an unexpected exception: {0}
Message.Explanation: The data source that was configured for use as a data store has produced an exception.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: INVALID_NUMBER_OF_STREAM_TABLES_SIMS1509=CWSIS1509E: An incorrect number of stream tables, {0}, were found.
Message.Explanation: There must be only one stream table.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the problem and try again.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TUPLE_TYPE_SIMS1502=CWSIS1502E: The tuple type, {0}, is not recognized as a valid type.
Message.Explanation: An internal error has occurred.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.UserResponse: Restart the messaging engine and try again.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_CLASSMAP_TABLE_REFERENCE_SIMS1534=CWSIS1534E: The class reference, {0}, was not resolved.
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine failed to find a class name that corresponds to the reference.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: CANNOT_COMMIT_COMPLETE_SIMS1004=CWSIS1004E: The transaction cannot be committed. The transaction is complete or completing.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to commit a transaction that has already been completed or is in the process of completing.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: EXPIRY_THREAD_ALREADY_RUNNING_SIMS2004=CWSIS2004E: The expiry daemon is already running.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TABLE_OPERATION_EXCEPTION_SIMS1526=CWSIS1526E: The item table, {0}, is not able to perform the operation. It is of type, {1}.
Message.Explanation: The item table cannot perform the requested operation because it is not of the correct type.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: FILE_STORE_UNEXPECTED_INITIALISATION_EXCEPTION_SIMS1591=CWSIS1591E: The file store has caught an unexpected exception during initialisation.

Message.MsgText: NUMBER_OF_TABLES_IN_USE_SIMS1571=CWSIS1571I: Data store table summary: Permanent {0}, temporary {1}.

Message.MsgText: DBLOCK_ATTEMPTING_SIMS1538=CWSIS1538I: The messaging engine, ME_UUID={0}, INC_UUID={1}, is attempting to obtain an exclusive lock on the data store.

Message.MsgText: FILE_STORE_CANNOT_FIND_LOG_FILE_SIMS1580=CWSIS1580E: The file store''s log file cannot be found in the provided location: {0}.

Message.MsgText: FILE_STORE_LOCK_ONE_OWNER_SIMS1566=CWSIS1566I: A single previous owner was found in the messaging engine''s file store, ME_UUID={0}, INC_UUID={1}

Message.MsgText: NUMBER_OF_TABLES_PREVIOUS_SIMS1572=CWSIS1572I: Data store table summary before configuration change: Permanent {0}, temporary {1}.

Message.MsgText: DBLOCK_LOST_SIMS1594=CWSIS1594I: The messaging engine, ME_UUID={0}, INC_UUID={1}, has lost the lock on the data store.

This may be due to a connectivity problem between the messaging engine and the database server or that another instance of the messaging engine has started and taken control of the tables.

Message.MsgText: FILE_STORE_LOCK_ACQUIRED_SIMS1563=CWSIS1563I: The messaging engine, ME_UUID={0}, INC_UUID={1}, has acquired an exclusive lock on the file store.
